    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your <strong>potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into fries</p><p>Add the <strong>fries</strong> to a <strong>baking</strong> <strong>paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/king-prawn-toast-sandwich-with-quick-pickled-slaw-and-sweet-potato-fries/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the fries are cooking, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/king-prawn-toast-sandwich-with-quick-pickled-slaw-and-sweet-potato-fries/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Drain, then chop your <strong>king prawns</strong> until they are very finely minced (keep chopping until they become sticky!)</p><p>Combine the <strong>minced</strong> <strong>prawns</strong> in a bowl with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped coriander </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and your <strong>soy sauce </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>king</strong> <strong>prawn toast mix</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/king-prawn-toast-sandwich-with-quick-pickled-slaw-and-sweet-potato-fries/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine most of your <strong>mayo </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)<strong> </strong>and your <strong>sriracha </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) in a small bowl \u2013 this is your <strong>sriracha mayo</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>carrot & cabbage slaw mix </strong>to<strong> </strong>a separate bowl with your <strong>rice vinegar</strong>, <strong>remaining chopped coriander </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> sugar</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and set aside to pickle \u2013 this is your <strong>quick-pickled slaw</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/king-prawn-toast-sandwich-with-quick-pickled-slaw-and-sweet-potato-fries/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut your <strong>ciabatta[s] </strong>in half</p><p>Spread the <strong>king</strong> <strong>prawn toast mix </strong>onto each <strong>ciabatta base </strong>(save the lid for later!)<strong> </strong>\u2013<strong> </strong>this is your <strong>king</strong> <strong>prawn ciabatta</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/king-prawn-toast-sandwich-with-quick-pickled-slaw-and-sweet-potato-fries/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>king</strong> <strong>prawn ciabatta</strong>, prawn-side down and cook for 5 min, then flip and cook for a further 2 min on the other side, or until the prawns are cooked through and the toast is golden \u2013 this is your <strong>king prawn toast[s]</strong></p><p>Once done, transfer the <strong>king</strong> <strong>prawn</strong> <strong>toast[s] </strong>to kitchen paper to drain</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/king-prawn-toast-sandwich-with-quick-pickled-slaw-and-sweet-potato-fries/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, spread the <strong>remaining mayo </strong>over the top of your <strong>ciabatta lid[s]</strong> and sprinkle over your <strong>toasted sesame seeds</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>ciabatta lid[s] </strong>to a baking tray and put the tray in the oven for 4-5 or until the ciabatta is starting to brown \u2013 this is your <strong>sesame ciabatta lid</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/king-prawn-toast-sandwich-with-quick-pickled-slaw-and-sweet-potato-fries/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top the <strong>king prawn</strong> <strong>toast</strong> with a dollop of <strong>sriracha mayo</strong>, some <strong>quick-pickled slaw </strong>and the <strong>sesame ciabatta lid </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>king prawn toast sandwich</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>king</strong> <strong>prawn toast sandwich </strong>with the <strong>fries </strong>and any <strong>remaining quick-pickled slaw </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
